    "m_SourceType": 1,
    "m_FunctionName": "SplitToning",
    "m_FunctionSource": "",
    "m_FunctionSourceUsePragmas": true,
    "m_FunctionBody": "// Girişler: In (Vector3), Shadows (Vector3), Highlights (Vector3), Balance (Float -100..100)\r\n// Çıkış: Out (Vector3)\r\n\r\nfloat balance = Balance / 100.0;\r\n\r\n// Unity bunu (Adobe ile uyum için) gamma uzayında yapar\r\nfloat3 c = pow(max(In, 1e-5), 1.0 / 2.2);\r\n\r\nfloat luma = saturate(dot(saturate(c), float3(0.2126729, 0.7151522, 0.0721750)) + balance);\r\nfloat3 sh = lerp(0.5, Shadows, 1.0 - luma);    // gölgelerde Shadows tonu\r\nfloat3 hi = lerp(0.5, Highlights, luma);       // highlight'larda Highlights tonu\r\n\r\n// soft light x2 (önce gölge, sonra highlight)\r\nfloat3 r1, r2;\r\nr1 = 2.0*c*sh + c*c*(1.0 - 2.0*sh);\r\nr2 = sqrt(c)*(2.0*sh - 1.0) + 2.0*c*(1.0 - sh);\r\nc = lerp(r1, r2, step(0.5, sh));\r\n\r\nr1 = 2.0*c*hi + c*c*(1.0 - 2.0*hi);\r\nr2 = sqrt(c)*(2.0*hi - 1.0) + 2.0*c*(1.0 - hi);\r\nc = lerp(r1, r2, step(0.5, hi));\r\n\r\nOut = pow(max(c, 0.0), 2.2);"
}

